# Firebase SQL Connect Constraints

## Operation Strategy
- Default: Native GraphQL (auto-generated queries/mutations). Type-safe, schema-enforced.
- Native SQL ONLY when explicitly required: PostGIS, window functions, complex aggregations. Uses `_select`/`_execute` with positional params `$1`.

## Schema Rules
- `schema/schema.gql`: types with `@table`, `@col`, `@default`, `@ref` for relations.
- `connector/queries.gql`: `@auth(level: ...)` on every operation — PUBLIC, USER_ANON, USER, NO_ACCESS.
- `connector/mutations.gql`: `_insert`, `_update`, `_upsert`, `_delete`. `@transaction` for atomic multi-step.
- Realtime: `@refresh` directive with CEL conditions.

## Validation
- Run `npx -y firebase-tools@latest dataconnect:compile` after schema/operation changes.
- Generated schema in `.dataconnect/schema/main/` — review before deploy.

## SDK Generation
- Configure in `connector.yaml`: `generate.javascriptSdk` with `outputDir` and `package`.
- Run `npx -y firebase-tools@latest dataconnect:sdk:generate`.
